    <h2 class="normal mt5 mb0">Getting Started</h2>
    <p>After making wine at Caymus for a few years, Randy decided it was time to strike out on his own. In 1978 he and Lori purchased the “Trailer Vinyard” and began farming 51/2 acres of Cabernet in their “free time”.   The next year Randy harvested 9 tons of fruit from the Trailer and Frank vineyards and then bought another 3 tons from Beatty.  When all was said and done he had 660 cases of 750mls, 28 cases of magnums, and 53 five liter bottles.</p>
    <p>Dunn Vineyards begins &hellip;</p>
