    <p>Things happened quickly after that. 1981 marked the bonding of the  winery in Angwin. And by 1984 the ATF approved the Howell Mountain AVA.   [[ talk about living in the White House — was there a trailer before that?]</p>
    <p>While they were getting the winery off the ground, the Dunns were also building a family.  Both Jenny and Kristina were born as in these years.  As the family outgrew the Western Union building, they started building their new family home on the property.  After moving into “the brown house”, the  White House became the dedicated spot for Dunn Vineyards.  Soon after, Randy had caves dug into the mountain beneath the office.</p>
